  <link rel="match" href="grammar-error-001-ref.html"><html>


  <style>
  div
    {
      font-size: 300%;
    }

  div::grammar-error
    {
      color: maroon;
      text-decoration: underline dotted fuchsia;
    }
  </style>

  <p>PREREQUISITE: User agent needs to have an enabled and capable grammar error module. If it does not, then this test does not apply to such user agent.

  <link rel="author" title="Gérard Talbot" href="http://www.gtalbot.org/BrowserBugsSection/css21testsuite/"><link rel="author" title="Gérard Talbot" href="http://www.gtalbot.org/BrowserBugsSection/css21testsuite/"><link rel="author" title="Gérard Talbot" href="http://www.gtalbot.org/BrowserBugsSection/css21testsuite/">Test passes if each glyph of "thing" is maroon and if "thing" is underlined with a fuchsia dotted line.

  <div contenteditable="true">Many thing can happen.</div>
